sql:
SELECT max_speed AS max_speed_achieved
FROM trips
WHERE trip_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(trip_id) AS total_trips
FROM user_trips
WHERE user_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
; This query assumes that the tables (trips, trip_data, vehicles, sensors, sensor_data, control_systems, control_data) are properly set up and that the vehicle ID is consistently used as a unique identifier for each vehicle across all tables; 
; The concept of "maintenance interval" is used to determine the time between the last and next scheduled maintenance for each vehicle;
; The query calculates average and maximum values for various metrics (speed, acceleration, curvature, etc.) from both trip data and sensor data to provide a comprehensive overview of vehicle performance.

sql:
SELECT SUM(total_distance) AS total_distance_covered
FROM user_trips
WHERE user_id = 1;

SELECT SUM(total_distance) AS total_distance, AVG(average_speed) AS average_speed
FROM user_trips
WHERE user_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
User with user_id = 1 refers to a user who has a unique identifier of 1 in the database; 
Average trip speed refers to the average speed of a user's trips; 
Sensor battery level refers to the battery level of the sensor during the user's trips.

sql:
SELECT trip_id, total_distance
FROM trips
ORDER BY total_distance DESC;
